<item>
  <title>ASSOCIATE PROFESSOR IN CARDIOLOGY - INTERNAL MEDICINE</title>
  <link>https://www.ub.bw/connect/job-opportunities/associate-professor-cardiology-internal-medicine</link>
  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;ASSOCIATE PROFESSOR IN CARDIOLOGY - INTERNAL MEDICINE&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;a title="View user profile." href="https://www.ub.bw/user/2371" lang="" about="https://www.ub.bw/user/2371" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" class="username" xml:lang=""&gt;mfetane&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Mon, 15/08/2022 - 15:46&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-department field--type-entity-reference field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Department/Faculty&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Internal Medicine&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Fri, 26 Aug. 2022&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF MEDICINE - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF INTERNAL MEDICINE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: FM/DIM 02/2022 -&lt;span&gt;  ASSOCIATE PROFESSOR IN CARDIOLOGY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;t&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;he successful candidate will: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;teach undergraduate medical students and postgraduate students; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(ii)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span&gt;conduct research and/or creative professional works in his/her areas of expertise and supervise undergraduate and postgraduate students’ research projects;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;provide service to the university, profession and community&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;provide clinical care in affiliated hospitals and; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(v)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span&gt;carry out any other duties as assigned by the head of department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;(i) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bachelor of Medicine/Bachelor of Surgery or other recognised medical qualification (MD); &lt;strong&gt;(ii) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;a specialist qualification in Cardiology Sub-Specialty; &lt;strong&gt;(iii) &lt;/strong&gt;the qualification must be registerable by the Botswana Health Professions Council with a specialist status; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;evidence of governance and social engagement; &lt;strong&gt;(v)&lt;/strong&gt; at least &lt;strong&gt;6 years&lt;/strong&gt; of relevant teaching experience at a University or comparable institution; &lt;strong&gt;(vi)&lt;/strong&gt; an excellent cumulative and sustained record of research and publication and experience in supervising students’ research projects; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;(vii)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; minimum of &lt;strong&gt;12&lt;/strong&gt; pieces of research products (articles, book chapters, peer reviewed conference proceedings) published by recognised publishers, &lt;strong&gt;6&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;12&lt;/strong&gt; publications must be articles in refereed/accredited journals in internationally recognised indexing databases; &lt;strong&gt;(viii)&lt;/strong&gt; paper/poster presentation at national and/or international conferences, depending on the discipline; &lt;strong&gt;(ix)&lt;/strong&gt; be lead and/or last author in at least two-thirds (&lt;strong&gt;4&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;6&lt;/strong&gt;) of the refereed journal publications; &lt;strong&gt;(x)&lt;/strong&gt; publications should be spread nationally and/or internationally and across journals; &lt;strong&gt;(xi)&lt;/strong&gt; some research impact, including but not limited to citations, the h-index, patents, policy applications, peer reviews, publications that are prescribed in texts in other institutions, etc (required in at least 2 of these); &lt;strong&gt;(xii)&lt;/strong&gt; recognised as being of at least national research or effective clinical professional standing (e.g. reviewer for refereed/accredited national and regional publishers, editorial board member of at least national publisher in a relevant field, invitation as keynote speaker at national and international conferences/symposia (required in at least 2 of these); &lt;strong&gt;(xiii)&lt;/strong&gt; research collaboration with other institutions or organisations; &lt;strong&gt;(xiv)&lt;/strong&gt; active maintenance of a licence to practice issued by the relevant professional licensing authority; successful supervision of 2 Masters students or co-supervision of 4 Masters students or supervision of 1 PhD student or co-supervision of 2 PhD students/post-doctoral/clinical research fellow supervision; &lt;strong&gt;(xv)&lt;/strong&gt; external examiner for Masters and/or PhD theses nationally and/or internationally; &lt;strong&gt;(xvi)&lt;/strong&gt; sustained professional research output; a minimum of 1.5 peer reviewed publications (e.g. journal article, book chapter, peer reviewed conference proceedings, etc.) per year&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;or new Creative Professional Work every 2 years in 6 years or since last promotion shall constitute sustained research output; &lt;strong&gt;(xvii)&lt;/strong&gt; the curriculum vitae (CV) should contain a detailed list of the publications; clearly specifying titles of publications, dates published, name(s) of publishers and name(s) of co-authors if any. Publications should be categorised into books, monographs, refereed journals, non-refereed journals, chapters in books, etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Attributes and skills required: (i) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;excellent communication and organisational skills; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; strong academic leadership skills and sympathy for the values and culture of the University; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; good management, human relations and sound analytical and coordinating skills. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The following will be added advantages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; sustained research activity; on-going internally and externally-funded research activity; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; research/clinical effectiveness awards and other forms of research recognition; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; supervisor of undergraduate and/or postgraduate scholarly projects. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; the University offers competitive salaries and benefits commensurate with qualifications and experience.  For more information on the University, please visit our website; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ub.bw/"&gt;www.ub.bw&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; applicants should address the stated qualification and provide any other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position.  They should quote the vacancy number of the post applied for, provide current CVs (including telephone, skype and e-mail address), certified true copies of educational certificates, transcripts, samples of the relevant publications, names, addresses and contact details of three referees and address these to: &lt;strong&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Faculty of Medicine, Corner of Notwane and Mabuto Road, University of Botswana, Private Bag 00713 Gaborone, Botswana; or Email &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;tshoganetsom@UB.AC.BW&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to:  &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; quote the vacancy number; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; position applied for, and; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; submit the references directly to the address stated above before the stipulated closing date.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be sent to&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;the&lt;strong&gt; Faculty of Medicine, Sir Ketumile Masire Teaching Hospital (SKMTH), 3rd Floor, Office F4003 or F4004&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that applications with incomplete information shall not be acknowledged.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 26 August 2022&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
