              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Internal Medicine&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Fri, 16 Oct. 2020&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF MEDICINE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF INTERNAL MEDICINE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;LECTURER/SENIOR LECTURER &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: FM/ IM 2/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; The successful candidate will be expected to: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; teach undergraduate medical students and graduate students in the Master of Medicine in Internal Medicine (MMed); and, &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; conduct research. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Senior lecturer:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should have:&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;(i)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; a Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS or MBChB) or MD degree or equivalent; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; a formal degree qualification as a specialist in Internal Medicine; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; the qualification must be registerable by the Botswana Health Professions Council with a specialist status; &lt;strong&gt;(iv) &lt;/strong&gt;3 years of university teaching experience or equivalent; &lt;strong&gt;(v)&lt;/strong&gt; evidence of professional specialization in Internal Medicine and evidence of active license to practice (where appropriate)&lt;strong&gt;;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(vi)&lt;/strong&gt; a minimum of &lt;strong&gt;6&lt;/strong&gt; pieces of research products (e.g. articles, book chapters, peer reviewed conference proceedings etc.) published by recognized publishers, &lt;strong&gt;3 &lt;/strong&gt;of which must be articles in refereed/accredited journals in internationally recognized indexing databases. The remaining &lt;strong&gt;3&lt;/strong&gt; publications could be books, book chapters, peer reviewed conference proceedings etc. published by recognized publishers  OR evidence of clinical excellence (CE):  high patient/community satisfaction; evidence of community/clinical outreach for specialized referrals; demonstrated practice of evidence-based medicine/ community interventions; evidence of quality improvement initiatives; reduction of clinical errors; effective and skillful interdisciplinary clinical work or community based public health programs&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;(minimum of 2 CE outputs is required); 1 CE output is equivalent to 1 article; &lt;strong&gt;(vii)&lt;/strong&gt; sustained research output; a minimum of 1 peer reviewed publication per year OR new CE output every 2 years in 6 years; &lt;strong&gt;(viii)&lt;/strong&gt; paper/poster presentation at national and/or international conferences in any discipline in Internal medicine; &lt;strong&gt;(ix)&lt;/strong&gt; be first  and /or last author in at least half (2 of 3) refereed journal publications; &lt;strong&gt;(x)&lt;/strong&gt; publications should be spread nationally and/or internationally and across journals; &lt;strong&gt;(xi)&lt;/strong&gt; some research impact, including but not limited to citations, the h-index, patents, policy applications, peer reviews, publications that are prescribed texts in other institutions etc. (required, at least 1 of these); &lt;strong&gt;(xii)&lt;/strong&gt; recognized as being of at least national research standing (e.g. reviewer for refereed/ accredited national and regional publishers, editorial board member of at least national publisher in a relevant field, invitation as keynote speaker at national and international conferences/symposia (required in at least 1 of these&lt;strong&gt;);&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(xiii)&lt;/strong&gt; active maintenance of a license to practice issued by the relevant professional licensing authority; &lt;strong&gt;(xiv)&lt;/strong&gt; evidence of governance and social engagement. &lt;strong&gt;The following are added advantages: (i)&lt;/strong&gt; sustained research activity; on-going internally and/or externally funded research projects; &lt;strong&gt;(ii) &lt;/strong&gt;research/clinical effectiveness awards and other forms of research recognition; &lt;strong&gt;(iii) &lt;/strong&gt;examiner for undergraduate and/or postgraduate projects nationally; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; research collaboration with other institutions or organizations; &lt;strong&gt;(iv&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt; research collaboration with cognate disciplines in the University; &lt;strong&gt;(v)&lt;/strong&gt; Evidence of sub-specialization in internal medicine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lecturer:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should have:&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;(i)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; a Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS or MBChB) or MD degree or equivalent; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; a formal degree qualification as a specialist in Internal Medicine; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; the qualification must be registerable by the Botswana Health Professions Council with a specialist status; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; evidence of professional specialization in Internal Medicine and evidence of active license to practice (where appropriate)&lt;strong&gt;. The following will be added advantages: (i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;) &lt;/strong&gt;Evidence of sub-specialization in internal medicine; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;evidence of governance and social engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;; and, &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; of teaching at a university or comparable institution. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Attributes and skills required: (i) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent communication and organizational skills; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; Strong academic leadership skills and sympathy for the values and culture of the University; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; Good management, human relations, sound analytical and coordinating skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; The University offers competitive salaries and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the university determine their suitability for the position. They should provide current CV’s (including telephone and e-mail), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, and THREE (3) reference letters.  Applicants should inform their referees to:  (i)&lt;strong&gt; Quote the position applied for&lt;/strong&gt; (ii) &lt;strong&gt;submit their references directly to the address below&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Faculty of Medicine, Corner of Notwane and Mabuto Road, University of Botswana, Private Bag 00713 Gaborone, Botswana; or Email to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:nkangana@ub.ac.bw"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;nkangana@ub.ac.bw&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be sent to &lt;strong&gt;Faculty of Medicine, UB Teaching Hospital, 3rd Floor, Office F 4003&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

